   Document name: Michael Jackson's last days -
                  What really happened

   The last time this series focused on the "King of Pop", it was two years
   after he had been found not guilty of all charges in the child
   abuse/paedophilia trial, this programme is much more tragic. Jacques Peretti
   directs, writes and stars in this documentary focusing on the last days of
   Michael Jackson, before his tragic and result-unconfirmed death at the age
   of 50. Using archive footage and interviews with all people that knew him
   best, including doctors and lawyers, Peretti tries to get to the bottom of
   why Jackson was so stressed before the gigs he would have done in London's
   O2 Arena, and what could have killed him, e.g. overdose on painkiller
